---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const title = 'AI Health Coach | Build a Personal Health AI That Learns You';
const description = 'Train a personal health AI on your wearable data, labs, and supplements. The more you teach it, the smarter it gets, finding patterns your doctors miss and giving you real answers.';
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>

  <!-- ===== BANNER ===== -->
  <section class="banner-section">
    <div class="container" style="text-align:center;">
      <div class="banner-wrapper">
        <h2 class="banner-title">AI Health Coach App</h2>
        <img
          src="/assets/branding/Main Screen.png"
          alt="AI Health Coach - Elevate Your Health & Performance with personalized guidance based on your wearable data"
          class="banner-image"
          loading="eager"
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== HERO ===== -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="hero-split">
        <div class="hero-text">
          <div class="kicker">
            <span aria-hidden="true">&#9679;</span>
            Garmin &middot; WHOOP &middot; Oura &middot; Apple Health &middot; 57+ biomarkers
          </div>

          <h1>Your personal<br/>health LLM. Stop Guessing and Start Knowing!</h1>

          <p class="lead">
            AI Health Coach isn&rsquo;t just an app. It&rsquo;s a personal large language model
            trained on <em>your</em> wearable data, labs, and supplements.
            Feed it everything. Ask it anything. The more you teach it, the more it learns
            about your body, finding patterns your doctors miss and giving you answers nobody else can.
          </p>

          <div style="margin-top:8px;">
            <a class="btn primary btn-lg" href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdRhAStyQpK484QXvk2icOUqBqIVyzZFIQG8o_4thZX6WlnoA/viewform" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-track="cta-get-the-app">
              Get Started Free &rarr;
            </a>
          </div>
          <p class="small" style="margin-top:10px;">
            Available now on Android &amp; iOS. Start training your AI in minutes.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="hero-screenshot">
          <div class="phone-frame">
            <img src="/screenshots/dashboard-scores.png" alt="AI Health Coach dashboard showing Biological Age, Longevity Score, Sleep Debt alert, and HRV trends" loading="eager" />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== THE PROBLEM ===== -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="card pad" style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto; text-align:center;">
        <h2 style="margin-top:0;">Get real insights and suggestions</h2>
        <div class="problem-grid">
          <div class="problem-item">
            <div class="problem-icon">0</div>
            <p>ChatGPT and Google give generic health advice based on population averages, not <em>your</em> data</p>
          </div>
          <div class="problem-item">
            <div class="problem-icon">?</div>
            <p>Your doctor glances at labs for 5 minutes and says &ldquo;everything looks fine&rdquo; while you feel terrible</p>
          </div>
          <div class="problem-item">
            <div class="problem-icon">5+</div>
            <p>Your health data is scattered across apps that never talk to each other. No one connects the dots</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="sub" style="margin: 18px auto 0; text-align:center;">
          You don&rsquo;t need another app. You need a personal health LLM that actually <em>knows</em> you.
          One that gets smarter every day you use it.
          <strong>That&rsquo;s AI Health Coach.</strong>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== REAL RESULTS ===== -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 style="text-align:center;">Real results. Not hypotheticals.</h2>
      <p class="sub" style="text-align:center; margin: 0 auto 24px;">
        This isn&rsquo;t a pitch deck. These are real discoveries made by training an AI on real health data.
      </p>

      <div class="grid cols-2" style="max-width:900px; margin:0 auto;">
        <div class="card pad">
          <h3 style="margin-top:0;">The iron deficiency no one caught</h3>
          <p>
            After 2 years of declining energy and stamina on TRT, the HRT clinic kept saying
            &ldquo;your bloodwork looks amazing.&rdquo; AI Health Coach connected what they didn&rsquo;t.
            Frequent blood donations required on TRT were depleting iron stores.
          </p>
          <div class="lab-proof">
            <img src="/screenshots/ferritin-lab.png" alt="Lab results showing Ferritin at 18 ng/mL - flagged Low against reference range of 30-400" loading="lazy" />
            <p class="small" style="margin:8px 0 0; text-align:center;">
              <strong>Ferritin: 18 ng/mL</strong> Flagged Low. Reference range: 30&ndash;400.
            </p>
          </div>
          <p>
            <strong>The fix:</strong> Iron bisglycinate 50mg twice daily with Vitamin C.
            Six weeks later, energy and stamina returning to baseline.
          </p>
          <p class="small" style="margin-bottom:0;">
            <em>The data was there the whole time. AI Health Coach just knew what to look for.</em>
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="card pad">
          <h3 style="margin-top:0;">The missing hormone protocol</h3>
          <p>
            A clinic suggested dropping HCG from a TRT regimen, saying it wasn&rsquo;t needed.
            Over the following years: strength declined, libido disappeared, mood tanked.
            &ldquo;Is this all there is?&rdquo;
          </p>
          <div class="lab-proof">
            <img src="/screenshots/lh-fsh-lab.png" alt="Lab results showing LH at less than 0.3 mIU/mL and FSH at less than 0.3 mIU/mL - both flagged Low" loading="lazy" />
            <p class="small" style="margin:8px 0 0; text-align:center;">
              <strong>LH: &lt;0.3</strong> (ref 1.7&ndash;8.6) &nbsp;&bull;&nbsp; <strong>FSH: &lt;0.3</strong> (ref 1.5&ndash;12.4) Both bottomed out.
            </p>
          </div>
          <p>
            <strong>AI Health Coach flagged it:</strong> Removing HCG crashed LH and FSH levels,
            hormones critical for mood, libido, and overall well-being. Those markers told the real story.
          </p>
          <p class="small" style="margin-bottom:0;">
            <em>Back on HCG. Starting to feel like himself again.</em>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="sub" style="text-align:center; margin: 24px auto 0;">
        Two real problems. Two real answers. Both missed by clinics. Both caught by AI Health Coach
        because it had been trained on the full picture.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== HOW YOUR AI LEARNS ===== -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 id="how-it-works" style="text-align:center;">The more you teach it, the smarter it gets</h2>
      <p class="sub" style="text-align:center; margin: 0 auto 24px;">
        AI Health Coach doesn&rsquo;t start smart. <em>You</em> make it smart. Every data point, every lab result,
        every check-in trains your personal health LLM to understand your body better than any generic tool ever could.
      </p>

      <div class="grid cols-4">
        <div class="feature" style="text-align:center;">
          <div class="problem-icon" style="margin:0 auto 8px;">Day 1</div>
          <h3>Connect &amp; baseline</h3>
          <p>Sync your wearables and upload your first labs. Your AI establishes your personal baselines:
             HRV, sleep architecture, biomarker ranges, supplement stack.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature" style="text-align:center;">
          <div class="problem-icon" style="margin:0 auto 8px;">Week 2</div>
          <h3>First patterns emerge</h3>
          <p>Your AI starts finding connections: which supplements correlate with better recovery,
             how your sleep affects next-day HRV, what training load your body can handle.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature" style="text-align:center;">
          <div class="problem-icon" style="margin:0 auto 8px;">Month 3</div>
          <h3>Deep understanding</h3>
          <p>With multiple lab panels and months of wearable data, your AI spots trends your doctor won&rsquo;t:
             biomarker velocity, supplement-to-outcome correlations, hidden deficiencies.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature" style="text-align:center;">
          <div class="problem-icon" style="margin:0 auto 8px;">Year 1+</div>
          <h3>Your health expert</h3>
          <p>A year of data creates a deeply personal health model. It knows your seasonal patterns, predicts
             recovery needs, and proactively flags issues before you feel them.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== WHAT YOUR AI LEARNS ===== -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 style="text-align:center;">What your AI builds knowledge about</h2>
      <p class="sub" style="text-align:center; margin: 0 auto 24px;">
        These aren&rsquo;t static dashboards. They&rsquo;re living scores that evolve as your AI learns more about you.
      </p>

      <div class="grid cols-3">
        <div class="feature">
          <h3>Longevity Index</h3>
          <p>A single 0&ndash;100 score across cardiovascular, metabolic, and recovery pillars.
             Built from your HRV, VO2max, sleep, ApoB, fasting glucose, hsCRP, and more. Letter graded A+ to F.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature">
          <h3>Biological Age</h3>
          <p>How old your body actually is vs. your birth certificate. Computed from 8 biomarkers,
             or import epigenetic clock results from TruAge, Elysium, or GrimAge.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature">
          <h3>Metabolic Health Score</h3>
          <p>0&ndash;100 score from metabolic syndrome criteria: fasting glucose, HbA1c, triglycerides, HDL,
             and waist circumference. Updates in real time as new data comes in.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature">
          <h3>Cardiovascular Age</h3>
          <p>Your heart&rsquo;s functional age based on VO2max, resting heart rate, HRV trends, and ApoB.
             See which factors are aging you and which are keeping you young.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature">
          <h3>Recovery Score</h3>
          <p>Daily 0&ndash;100 readiness score combining HRV, sleep quality, soreness, stress, and training load.
             Know when to push hard and when to back off.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature">
          <h3>Centenarian Decathlon</h3>
          <p>Grip strength, single-leg balance, VO2max, dead hang, wall sit. The functional fitness markers
             that predict how well you&rsquo;ll move at 80. Tracked and scored.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== AI FEATURES ===== -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 style="text-align:center;">Ask it anything. It answers with <em>your</em> data.</h2>
      <p class="sub" style="text-align:center; margin: 0 auto 24px;">
        Not a generic chatbot. AI Health Coach is a personal LLM grounded in your wearable data, labs, supplements, and history,
        and it gets more useful every time you interact with it.
      </p>

      <div class="screenshot-row">
        <div class="screenshot-row-content">
          <div class="grid" style="gap:16px;">
            <div class="feature">
              <h3>Ask your AI anything</h3>
              <p>&ldquo;Why has my energy been low for 3 weeks?&rdquo; Get answers grounded in your actual data,
                 not WebMD articles. Your AI cross-references labs, wearables, supplements, and check-ins
                 to find what&rsquo;s really going on.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="feature">
              <h3>Lab interpretation that goes deeper</h3>
              <p>Upload a lab PDF and your AI doesn&rsquo;t just flag out-of-range values.
                 It compares against your history, spots trends, and connects results to your symptoms
                 and supplement stack. 57+ biomarkers tracked over time.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="feature">
              <h3>N=1 pattern detection</h3>
              <p>&ldquo;Your HRV is 18% higher on mornings after 90+ min of deep sleep.&rdquo;
                 The more data you feed it, the more patterns it finds that are unique to your biology.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="feature">
              <h3>Proactive alerts</h3>
              <p>Your AI doesn&rsquo;t wait for you to ask. It flags when HRV drops 10%+ from baseline,
                 when training load is spiking dangerously, when labs are getting stale, or when something
                 in your data doesn&rsquo;t add up.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="screenshot-row-image">
          <div class="phone-frame">
            <img src="/screenshots/dashboard-wearables.png" alt="AI Health Coach dashboard showing HRV, RHR, Sleep metrics with trend charts and Ask AI button" loading="lazy" />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== FEED YOUR AI ===== -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 style="text-align:center;">Feed your AI everything</h2>
      <p class="sub" style="text-align:center; margin: 0 auto 24px;">
        Every data point makes your AI smarter. The more you give it, the better it understands you.
      </p>

      <div class="grid cols-3">
        <div class="feature">
          <h3>57+ lab biomarkers</h3>
          <p>Lipids, hormones, thyroid, glucose, inflammation, vitamins, liver, kidney,
             all with longevity-optimal ranges, not just clinical &ldquo;normal.&rdquo;</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature">
          <h3>Supplements &amp; protocols</h3>
          <p>Log your full stack with doses, frequency, and timing. Your AI tracks what you&rsquo;re taking
             and correlates it against your biomarkers and how you feel.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature">
          <h3>Workouts &amp; training load</h3>
          <p>Log sets, reps, and weight. Track 1RM progress. Your AI monitors acute vs. chronic training load
             to tell you when to push and when to recover.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature">
          <h3>Fasting intelligence</h3>
          <p>Start a fast and watch your stage progress: digestive, fat burning, ketosis, autophagy, deep autophagy.
             Your AI learns how fasting affects your recovery and performance.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature">
          <h3>Sauna &amp; cold exposure</h3>
          <p>Log thermal sessions by type, duration, and temperature.
             Your AI correlates sessions with HRV and recovery patterns.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature">
          <h3>Daily check-ins</h3>
          <p>Quick 30-second daily log: mood, energy, stress, soreness, stamina.
             This subjective data is critical. It&rsquo;s how your AI learns what your numbers <em>feel</em> like.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== RECOMMENDATIONS ENGINE ===== -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="screenshot-row screenshot-row-reverse">
        <div class="screenshot-row-content">
          <h2 style="margin-top:0;">Your AI coaches you daily</h2>
          <p class="sub" style="margin: 0 0 20px;">
            As it learns your patterns, its guidance gets more specific, more personal, and more useful.
          </p>

          <div class="grid" style="gap:16px;">
            <div class="feature">
              <h3>Daily action plan</h3>
              <p>Wake up to a prioritized list built from last night&rsquo;s sleep, your training load, and this week&rsquo;s trends.
                 &ldquo;Recovery is low, swap today&rsquo;s strength session for Zone 2.&rdquo;</p>
            </div>
            <div class="feature">
              <h3>Monthly deep dive</h3>
              <p>AI-generated monthly report: what improved, what declined, which habits correlated with your best weeks,
                 and 3 specific priorities for the next 30 days.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="feature">
              <h3>Smart goal suggestions</h3>
              <p>Your AI analyzes your last 14 days and suggests the top 3 goals ranked by impact.
                 &ldquo;Your HRV of 35ms suggests under-recovery. Sleep optimization should be priority #1.&rdquo;</p>
            </div>
            <div class="feature">
              <h3>AI-built protocols</h3>
              <p>Accept a goal and get a full evidence-based plan: daily actions, weekly schedule,
                 which metrics to track, and what success looks like. Then your AI monitors the results.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="screenshot-row-image screenshot-stack">
          <div class="phone-frame">
            <img src="/screenshots/daily suggestions.jpg" alt="AI Health Coach Today's Action Items - Keep intensity moderate today based on HRV and sleep data" loading="lazy" />
          </div>
          <div class="phone-frame">
            <img src="/screenshots/workout suggestions based on recovery data.jpg" alt="AI Health Coach Workouts - Recovery readiness score with workout schedule adjusted based on recovery zone" loading="lazy" />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== WHAT MOVES THE NEEDLE ===== -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 style="text-align:center;">Your AI finds what actually works for you</h2>
      <p class="sub" style="text-align:center; margin: 0 auto 24px;">
        You take 12 supplements, do sauna 3x/week, and fast 16 hours a day. But which of those
        actually matter <em>for you</em>? Your AI figures that out.
      </p>

      <div class="grid cols-3">
        <div class="feature">
          <h3>Supplement &harr; biomarker correlation</h3>
          <p>&ldquo;You started NMN 500mg/day 3 months ago. Since then, your NAD proxy markers improved 22%.&rdquo;
             Your AI runs automatic before-vs-after analysis for every supplement matched to the biomarkers it targets.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature">
          <h3>Behavior &harr; recovery correlation</h3>
          <p>&ldquo;You&rsquo;re 34% more energetic on days after taking magnesium.&rdquo;
             &ldquo;Sauna sessions correlate with +12% HRV the following morning.&rdquo;
             Correlations surfaced as plain-English insights.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature">
          <h3>Sleep &harr; performance patterns</h3>
          <p>&ldquo;On nights with 90+ min deep sleep, your next-day HRV averages 18% higher.&rdquo;
             Your AI finds your personal sleep-performance formula.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature">
          <h3>Experiment reports</h3>
          <p>Finish an 8-week protocol and your AI generates a narrative: &ldquo;HRV up 15%, sleep score up 8%,
             energy check-ins improved 0.7 points. Confidence: moderate.&rdquo; Real data, not vibes.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature">
          <h3>Biomarker velocity tracking</h3>
          <p>Not just where your labs are today, but which direction they&rsquo;re headed.
             Trend lines across 3, 6, and 12 months. Your AI flags when trajectories change.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature">
          <h3>Anonymous benchmarking</h3>
          <p>&ldquo;Your VO2max (52) is in the 78th percentile for males aged 38&ndash;42.&rdquo;
             Compare your key metrics to the app&rsquo;s user cohort, age and sex matched.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== INTEGRATIONS ===== -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container" style="text-align:center;">
      <h2>Data sources that train your AI</h2>
      <p class="sub" style="text-align:center; margin: 0 auto 16px;">
        Every integration is another stream of training data. Automatic sync, no manual entry.
      </p>
      <div class="pills" style="justify-content:center; margin-top:16px;">
        <a class="pill pill-lg" href="/garmin">Garmin Connect</a>
        <a class="pill pill-lg" href="/whoop">WHOOP</a>
        <span class="pill pill-lg">Oura</span>
        <span class="pill pill-lg">Apple Health</span>
        <span class="pill pill-lg">Android Health Connect</span>
      </div>
      <p class="small" style="margin-top:14px;">
        Plus: lab PDF upload (LabCorp, Quest, etc.), genetic reports (23andMe, InsideTracker),
        CGM data, DEXA scans, and manual biomarker entry.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== TRAIN THROUGH EXPERIMENTS ===== -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="card pad" style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto;">
        <h2 style="margin-top:0; text-align:center;">Train your AI through experiments</h2>
        <p class="sub" style="text-align:center; margin: 0 auto 18px;">
          Design a protocol. Your AI observes the outcomes and updates its understanding of what works for you.
        </p>
        <div class="grid cols-3">
          <div style="text-align:center;">
            <div class="problem-icon" style="margin:0 auto 8px;">1</div>
            <p class="small"><strong>Design</strong><br/>Define your protocol: supplements, training changes, nutrition, thermal therapy. Set doses, timing, and duration.</p>
          </div>
          <div style="text-align:center;">
            <div class="problem-icon" style="margin:0 auto 8px;">2</div>
            <p class="small"><strong>Track</strong><br/>Log daily adherence. Your AI monitors HRV, sleep, biomarkers, and check-ins throughout the experiment.</p>
          </div>
          <div style="text-align:center;">
            <div class="problem-icon" style="margin:0 auto 8px;">3</div>
            <p class="small"><strong>Learn</strong><br/>Your AI generates a report and integrates the findings. Next time, its recommendations are smarter because of what you taught it.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== PRIVACY ===== -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container" style="text-align:center;">
      <h2>Your AI. Your data. No one else&rsquo;s.</h2>
      <div class="grid cols-3" style="max-width:800px; margin:12px auto 0;">
        <div class="feature" style="text-align:center;">
          <h3>AES-256 encryption</h3>
          <p>Lab values, supplement names, notes, and genetic data encrypted at rest. Biometric unlock required to view.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature" style="text-align:center;">
          <h3>You control access</h3>
          <p>Connect and disconnect wearables anytime. Delete all data with one tap. Full CSV/JSON export available.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature" style="text-align:center;">
          <h3>Share on your terms</h3>
          <p>Generate time-limited, read-only links to share with your doctor or coach. No one else sees your data.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== FOUNDER ===== -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="card pad founder-card">
        <h2 style="margin-top:0;">Why I built this</h2>
        <p>
          I was on TRT for 6 years, tracking everything across Garmin, bloodwork panels, and supplement logs.
          For the last 2 years my energy and stamina were declining. Every visit to the clinic:
          &ldquo;Your bloodwork looks amazing.&rdquo; But I felt terrible.
        </p>
        <p>
          I didn&rsquo;t need another app. I needed an AI that could see the full picture.
          One I could teach about my body, my protocols, and my history. So I built it.
          Within weeks it caught what the clinic missed for 2 years: iron deficiency from required blood
          donations, and hormone imbalances from a protocol change they said &ldquo;wouldn&rsquo;t matter.&rdquo;
        </p>
        <p>
          AI Health Coach isn&rsquo;t a replacement for your doctor. It&rsquo;s a personal health AI
          that you train with your own data. The more you teach it, the better it knows you.
          And when something&rsquo;s off, it doesn&rsquo;t tell you everything looks fine. It tells you why.
        </p>
        <p style="margin-bottom:0;">
          <strong>- Joe, Founder</strong><br/>
          <a href="https://www.instagram.com/josephtolandsr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="color: var(--blue);">
            Follow the journey on Instagram &rarr;
          </a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== BOTTOM CTA ===== -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container" style="text-align:center;">
      <h2>Start training AI Health Coach today</h2>
      <p class="sub" style="text-align:center; margin: 0 auto 20px; max-width:50ch;">
        The sooner you start feeding it data, the sooner your personal health LLM starts finding answers.
        AI Health Coach is waiting to learn you.
      </p>

      <a class="btn primary btn-lg" href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdRhAStyQpK484QXvk2icOUqBqIVyzZFIQG8o_4thZX6WlnoA/viewform" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-track="cta-get-the-app">
        Get Started Free &rarr;
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== COMPLIANCE ===== -->
  <section class="section" style="padding-top:0;">
    <div class="container" style="text-align:center;">
      <div class="small" style="margin-top:10px;">
        <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a> &middot;
        <a href="/data-deletion">Data Deletion</a> &middot;
        <a href="/terms">Terms of Use</a> &middot;
        <a href="/garmin">Garmin Integration Details</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
